232 HORACE ’

haec Iovem sentire deosque cunctos

spem bonam certamque domum reporto,

doctus et Phoebi chorus et Dianae 75 dicere laudes.

70. quindecim (s): see on Odes 4. 1. 10, 11.

71. curat: there should be stress; see on Odes 4. 9. 26.

amicas (ps) i.e. ‘ears that are friendly] Compare Livy 34. 5. 13 superbas (ps), me dius fidius, aures habemus, and malas at Epod. 3. 6, 7. See too P. 21.

73. cunctos (pp) has stress.

75, 76. Phoebi is set in front of chorus in artificia] contrast to Dianae. The genitives go with both chorus and laudes.
